  "title": "Desktop Support Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Job Role/Level\tDesktop Engineers</p><p>Preferred Skills</p><p>Brief Job Description\tKey Responsibilities:</p><p>•\tProvide first-level technical support for desktop computing environment, including hardware, software, and peripherals troubleshooting</p><p>•\tFollow and execute Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) for various technical support scenarios and change management processes</p><p>•\tMaintain detailed documentation of all support activities, incidents, and resolutions on designated platforms</p><p>•\tHandle user requests and incidents through email communication, ensuring proper tracking and timely updates</p><p>•\tSupport end-user computing device (EUCD) compliance and management, including asset tracking and security policies</p><p>•\tProcess administrative paperwork for IT equipment deployment, replacement, and disposal</p><p>•\tGenerate regular reports on support metrics and incident resolution status</p><p>Required Skills:</p><p>•\tStrong technical knowledge of Windows operating systems and Microsoft Office suite</p><p>•\tExperience with IT service management tools and ticketing systems</p><p>•\tExcellent documentation and administrative skills</p><p>•\tGood communication skills in both written and verbal English</p><p>•\tAbility to work independently and follow established procedures</p><p>•\tBasic understanding of IT security practices and compliance requirements</p><p>Work Location\tCustomer office</p><p></p>",
